title: For Sale/Trade:  HK G3 clone
postcontent: I have a HK G3 clone that was built on a gewehr werks receiver.  It has a clipped and pinned SEF trigger housing,  not that hideous wrap around shelf like ptr.  The bolt gap is .012, bolt carrier is a FA that has been converted.  I have put roughly 200 rounds down range without any issues with cycling, extraction or feeding with the after market mag.  I was told that in order to run G3 mags I would need to change 3 more items on the 922r list, as far as I can tell and was told, the muzzle brake, barrel, receiver, and the sear have been changed to 922r parts.  Quite accurate for a 18 inch barrel, sights are not canted, but the charge tube is not exactly centered in the front ring.  Don't shoot this weapon very often so I figured it's time to give it to a good home.
